The final sample comprised 28,006 firm-year observations from 4841 listed companies. Following prior literature(Li et al., 2024;
Shiyyab et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2024b), we control for firm-specific characteristics that may influence the relationship between AI
focus and operational efficiency. These control variables include firm age and size, leverage, tangible and intangible asset ratios,
liquidity, cash flow, and the market-to-book ratio. In addition, to account for industry structure effects, we incorporate the
Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI)(Lijesen, 2004), which helps distinguish whether the observed outcomes are driven by
industry-level concentration or firm-level behavior. Table 1 presents the measurements of all variables. Appendix 1 summarizes the
descriptive statistics for the industry, year, and variables.
3.2. Modeling
Following the framework of Mishra et al. (2022), we constructed a system of simultaneous equations and estimated it using the
three-stage least squares (3SLS) method(Adewuyi and Awodumi, 2017; Mishra et al., 2022; Zou et al., 2023) while mitigating potential
endogeneity concerns(Rutz and Watson, 2019).
