5. Conclusion
This study investigates the impact of firms’ focus on AI, as reflected in their annual reports, on the operational efficiency of listed
Chinese firms. The results reveal that although discussions on AI have increased significantly in corporate reports, insufficient evidence
exists to support the relationship between AI focus and gross operational efficiency. In contrast, AI focus is negatively associated with
key performance indicators such as employee profitability, return on sales, and return on marketing investment. These findings suggest
that corporate emphasis on AI may function more as a market-signaling strategy than a reflection of substantive technological
implementation.
This study provides the first systematic evidence of the relationship between AI focus and operational efficiency among Chinese-
listed firms and contributes novel insights to the existing literature. These findings highlight the potential challenges Chinese firms
may face when AI focus into actual performance gains. Although the focus is on China, the implications extend beyond national
